@@WWIZARD@@W

Wizards are precision arcanists: patient theoreticians who break combat into
angles, timing windows, and controlled spell sequencing. If Sorcerers are
wildfire, Wizards are the scalpel.

@@WPassive class advantages@@W
  * @@wSpell critical chance@@W increases with Wizard levels
    (+0.1% per level, up to +10% at 100).
  * @@wRemort non-physical damage@@W gains Wizard scaling
    (+0.5% per level, up to +50% at 100).
  * @@wArcane healing throughput@@W improves for INT-based arcane healing
    (+2% per Wizard level, up to +200% at 100).

@@WUnique Wizard mechanics@@W
  * Access to @@wWizard stance@@W (dual-cast / no-hit caster posture).
  * Shares high-end arcane synergy with Sorcerer and Grand Magi progression.
  * Uses @@wIntelligence@@W as prime remort attribute.

@@WWizard reincarnation bonuses@@W
  * @@wWizard + Sorcerer remort reincarnations >= 20@@W unlocks
    @@wEquip Wand@@W permanently.

See also: @@mremort stance sorcerer grand_magi reincarnate@@W
